@group quick-connects
@endpoint DELETE /quick-connects/{InstanceId}/{QuickConnectId}
@desc Deletes a quick connect.   After calling DeleteUser, it's important to call DeleteQuickConnect to delete any records related to the deleted users. This will help you:   Avoid dangling resources that impact your service quotas.   Remove deleted users so they don't appear to agents as transfer options.   Avoid the disruption of other Amazon Connect processes, such as instance replication and syncing if you're using Amazon Connect Global Resiliency.
@required {InstanceId: str, QuickConnectId: str}

@endgroup

