@group views
@endpoint GET /views/{InstanceId}/{ViewId}
@desc Retrieves the view for the specified Amazon Connect instance and view identifier. The view identifier can be supplied as a ViewId or ARN.  $SAVED needs to be supplied if a view is unpublished. The view identifier can contain an optional qualifier, for example, &lt;view-id&gt;:$SAVED, which is either an actual version number or an Amazon Connect managed qualifier $SAVED | $LATEST. If it is not supplied, then $LATEST is assumed for customer managed views and an error is returned if there is no published content available. Version 1 is assumed for Amazon Web Services managed views.
@required {InstanceId: str, ViewId: str}
@returns(200) {View: View?{Id: str?, Arn: str?, Name: str?, Status: str?, Type: str?, Description: str?, Version: int?, VersionDescription: str?, Content: ViewContent?{InputSchema: str?, Template: str?, Actions: [str]?}, Tags: map<str, str>?: any, CreatedTime: str(timestamp)?, LastModifiedTime: str(timestamp)?, ViewContentSha256: str?}}

@endgroup

